title: For Sale:  SIG SAUER P226 EQUINOX ! Limited Production ! VERY RARE !
postcontent: Selling to fund other projects.Sig Sauer P226 Equinox 9mm- 2 magazines and EVERYTHING factory original included.- This gun is UNFIRED BRAND NEW IN BOXDETAILSThe Equinox® is the balance between day and night. The P226® Equinox features a two-tone accented Nitron® stainless steel slide with a lightweight black hard-anodized alloy frame. The contrast in color is achieved by the brush polished flats of the slide and nickel accents. The combination of the TRUGLO® Tritium Fiber Optic front sight and the rear SIGLITE® night sight provides excellent target acquisition, whether shooting day or night. To further enhance the low-light use, the Equinox comes equipped with an accessory rail. To complete the package, the Equinox comes with gray laminated wood grips with a perfect blend of checkering and stippling to enhance not only the form but the function. The 9mm Equinox is a non-cataloged model. It is my understanding (as far as my research would take me, feel free to search for yourself.) that this pistol is part of the first small number of factory guns that Sig Sauer accidentally cut the slides for 9mm and finished the guns instead of scrapping the slides. Should these come in stock again it may not be available again.The date on the side of the box printed on the SKU Label reads: 11-NOV-2013 (pictures upon request)ADDITIONAL INFORMATIONSKU E26R-9-EQCaliber 9mmManufacturer Sig SauerOverall Height 5.5 inOverall Width 1.5 inSight Radius 6.3 inBarrel Length (in) 4.4"Mag Capacity / Rounds 15rdNumber of Mags 2What makes this gun so rare? The Sig Sauer Equinox is ONLY produced in .40 S&W, this gun however, was made in 9mm. The story goes that Sig Sauer was starting the slides for a Equinox line production and accidentally used 9mm instead of 40 S&W. By the time the mistake was noticed there were already hundreds made. Instead of waisting all the slides and materials they decided to finish the 9mm equinox's and sell them. This pistol is one of these very few. Some say there were less than 300 made and very few if any remain untouched and unfired like this one is right now. This item is close to impossible to find and is surely a crown jewel for any gun collector.Osage County Gun, talking about a p229 they had for sale said: This is a non-cataloged item. Previously Sig Sauer made some P226 Equinoxes in 9mm because 9mm Equinox slides were built by accident and they finished the guns instead of destroying the slides. Those guns were never available again after that run. We are not sure if the same mistake happened with P229 slides and the factory finished the guns or if this is a limited short-term run of this configuration. We cannot guarantee we can get more once these are sold. OUT OF STOCKAny addition information or any addition pictures are available upon request, Please do not hesitate to ask anything!Email, Text or Call REDACTEDmust be 21 non felon Ohio resident.
